JOHANNESBURG – Lions coach Swys de Bruin has made eight changes for the team that will run out against the Crusaders in the Super Rugby at Emirates Airline Park on Sunday. Hacjivah Dayimani has been included at No 8. He has three Super Rugby caps under his belt and will pack down with Kwagga Smith, back at six, and Cyle Brink. Another youngster, Madosh Tambwe, will start at wing in the place of the injured Aphiwe Dyantyi. READ: Lions sign new sponsor for next three years Dillon Smit dons the No 9  jumper in his first start for Super Rugby this season. Corné Fourie makes his way onto the bench as replacement hooker. Lions team: 15 Andries Coetzee, 14 Sylvian Mahuza, 13 Lionel Mapoe, 12 Harold Vorster, 11 Madosh Tambwe, 10 Elton Jantjies, 9 Dillon Smit, 8 Hacjivah Dayimani, 7 Cyle Brink, 6 Kwagga Smith, 5 Franco Mostert, 4 Andries Ferreira, 3 Ruan Dreyer, 2 Malcolm Marx, 1 Dylan Smith Replacements: 16 Corne Fourie, 17 Jacques Van Rooyen, 18 Jacobie Adriaanse 19 Lourens Erasmus, 20 Marvin Orie, 21 Marnus Schoeman, 22 Howard Mnisi, 23 Shaun Reynolds African News Agency